Hello,
We are using check_disk v1.5 (nagios-plugins 1.5),
Our disk geometry:
  /dev/md127 on /EBS type ext3 (rw,noatime,nodiratime,_netdev)
  /EBS on /opt type none (rw,bind)

check executes with options:
  ./check_disk --warning=10% --critical=5% --iwarning=10% --icritical=5% --all --include-type=ext3 --include-type=ext4 --include-type=xfs -X tmpfs
and check ignores mount point /EBS because of "include-type" file system option.

We could use check with options:
  ./check_disk --warning=10% --critical=5% --iwarning=10% --icritical=5% --all --ignore-ereg-path=/run -X tmpfs -u GB
But it than could report errors like:
   /home/user/.gvs - Permission denied
   
   
We believe it is not correct to skip check of mount point that is mounted as bind.
Is it possible to fix that behavior ?
Thank you in advance!
